                            <comment id="17935492" author="JIRAUSER309000" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2025 12:02:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for looking into the issue. I have looked at the pull request #2317, and I have a question.&lt;br/&gt;
In CXF there is only single instance Timer &quot;DelayedCachedOutputStreamCleaner&quot; in an application from what I now see.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The single instance Timer is triggered at fixed interval, and it calls the clean() method, and that calls close() for all. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A new young Closeable in a CachedOutputStream that is just registered before the Timer is triggered, would be prematurely closed, don&apos;t you think?&#160; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; void clean(Collection&amp;lt;DelayedCloseable&amp;gt; closeables) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; (iterator.hasNext()) {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; DelayedCloseable next = iterator.next();
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// ...
&lt;/span&gt; &#160;  next.closeable.close();
  }
}&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17935503" author="reta" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2025 12:20:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ralphb&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ralphb&quot;&gt;ralphb&lt;/a&gt; , I think this assumption:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; The single instance Timer is triggered at fixed interval, and it calls the clean() method, and that calls close() for all.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is not strictly correct: the clean(...) will be called only for the &lt;b&gt;Closeable&lt;/b&gt;s that are expired. So no, the newly registered &lt;b&gt;Closeable&lt;/b&gt; will not be prematurely expired (timer runs at 0.5 of configured expiration delay). Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17935612" author="JIRAUSER309000" created="Fri, 14 Mar 2025 18:09:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right Andriy. I had overlooked that the &lt;b&gt;queue&lt;/b&gt; is a java.util.concurrent.DelayQueue. And queue.drainTo(closeables) only returns the expired Closeables. The junit tests helped to prove it. Thank you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
